Preheat your oven to 200°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of @water{for boiling} to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta. Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}(grated). Once boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%mins}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @diced chorizo{60%g} and stir-fry until it releases its oils, ~{1-2%mins}. Don't let it take on too much colour. Transfer the chorizo and its oil to a #small bowl{} with the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g}. Season with @ground black pepper{}, stir to combine then set aside.

Put your frying pan back on medium-high heat. Add the @olive oil{1%tsp} for the roux and the onion. Stir-fry until soft, ~{3-4%mins}, then stir in the @plain flour{2%tbsp}. Cook until it forms a paste consistency, ~{1-2%mins}. Gradually, stir in the @water{200%ml} for the sauce and the @chicken stock paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil, then simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%mins}. Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, then remove from the heat.

Add the @dried oregano{1%tsp} and Cheddar to the sauce and stir until well combined. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add the cooked pasta to the sauce and stir to combine. Add a splash of water to loosen it if needed. Transfer to an #ovenproof dish{} and sprinkle the chorizo crumb evenly over the top. Bake on the top shelf of your oven until the crumbs are golden, ~{5-6%mins}. Once cooked, remove from your oven and leave to stand.

Meanwhile, wash out your frying pan and pop it back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil. Halve any thick @tenderstem broccoli{150%g} stems lengthways. Once the pan is hot, add the broccoli and stir-fry for ~{1-2%mins}. Add the @garlic{1%clove} and fry for ~{1%minute} longer. Then add a splash of water and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}. Lower the heat to medium and allow to cook until the broccoli is tender, ~{4-5%mins}. Remove the pan from the heat.

Spoon the baked rigatoni into bowls and serve the broccoli alongside. Enjoy!